I have recently tested expected percentile rank(EPR) evaluation method proposed in the paper on the Movielens data set and a real world data set. However, I got a expected rank about 50% in both set, according to the paper, that means implicit ALS actually does not predict anything.

I am not sure if any evaluation has been done like this. 

How can we make sure that implicit ALS is implemented correctly in MLlib without checking code?

My thought on `SchemaResolutionMode` is that we may be able to hide implementation details on how we infer the schema by using `SchemaResolutionMode` in `jsonFile` and `jsonRDD`. If we expose `samplingRatio` in `jsonFile` and `jsonRDD`, when we have other methods to infer the schema (lazy resolution), we need to change existing interfaces or add new interfaces.

Yes, it would be good to find a way to automatically convert an event case class to and from JSON. The tricky thing here is we want the field names to be mnemonic, rather than what the corresponding case class parameters are named.
